10 An Act relating to the Pardon and Parole Board;
making an appropriation; stating purpose; providing
11 an effective date; and declaring an emergency.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. There is hereby appropriated to the Pardon and
16 Parole Board from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
17 General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for the fiscal year
18 ending June 30, 2027, the sum of Sixty-five Thousand Three Hundred
19 Thirty-three Dollars ($65,333.00) or so much thereof as may be
20 necessary to carry out the provisions established in Enrolled Senate
21 Bill No. 1330 of the 2nd Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
23 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
